race.description: Brad Ryan Qtis Three-Year-Old Maiden Plate
race.comment: VALOURI (14) is unlucky to still be a maiden finishing runner-up in both starts to date and strikes a very winnable assignment here in what could be a case of third time lucky. DASHING MARS (3) resumes here but has tuned up for this with a recent trial placing and gets a stack of weight relief with the 3kg claim. Include from the low draw. ENJECTOR (4) is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley and must be respected out of the Freedman barn. Top-three contender. FORGING AHEAD (5) makes some appeal despite the sticky draw. Shapes as one of the key each way players along with ODE TO BEAUTY (11).
